data.text:
This is the main article for Plant Island. For the category, see Category:Plant Island.

 Plant Island is a serene, sleepy paradise. Lie back and let the whisper of nature fill your ears. Breathe deep, and savor the intoxicating fragrance of flowers in bloom. Things change a little when Monsters arrive: Plant Island gets noisy. You won't be doing much napping then!   In-game description

About[]

Plant Island is the first island available to the player in My Singing Monsters. It is the first Natural Island and manifests the Plant Element . The island has a total of 66 Monsters and 145 Costumes. Monsters on this island can be placed on Gold Island or teleported to Shugabush Island, Seasonal Shanty, Ethereal Island, Mythical Island, or The Colossingum.

Song[]

Composed by: Dave Kerr, Kristian Bush (Shugabush) Sam Clark (Rare Wubbox) Tom Meikle (Epic Wubbox, the Colossal's song)

Plant Islands song plays at a speed of 140 beats per minute and plays in the key of C Harmonic Minor. The song is also available to download via the My Singing Monsters Soundtrack.

Plant Island's song can be described as a ballad, as the song is mostly basic and slow.

Plant Island has an ambience consisting of birds chirping and heavy wind.

The Colossal's Song[]

Audio Sample: https://mysingingmonsters.fandom.com/wiki/File:Colossal_Plant_Sample.mp3

The Colossal makes a low, mechanical drone noise that slowly builds up. This sound only occurs when The Colossal is awake, which can be done by placing the Coloss-Eye on Plant Island.

Parlsona: "Every Monster knows... how the plants grow!

And every Monster cares!

And they know how they shape and they feed them!

And they keep them alive!

Let's watch plants grow! (X2)"

Both: "Everything here is alive! (X2)"

Tawkerr: "They sleep when it gets cold.

And the leaves turn, they turn red and they turn gold.

They need sunlight and water and earth and the air to keep them alive.

That's how plants grow! (X2)"

And a note... becomes... a Monster!"

And then it splits, and makes a twin!

Then, there are more.

Look, across the landscape, and you'll find, it's just a bunch of plants! (Tawkerr echoing "a bunch of plants")"

The Monsters of Plant Island are of the Plant ( ), Earth ( ), Water ( ), Cold ( ), Plasma ( ), Electricity ( ), Legendary ( ), Spooktacle ( ), Mythical ( ), and Dipster ( ) elements. Since Plant Island lacks the Air ( ) Element, no Monster with that element can exist on it.

Obstacles[]

Main article: Obstacles

Removing the rocks and trees from the island earns the player Experience ( ) and it opens up space to place more Monsters, Decorations, or Structures. Removed obstacles are not gone permanently; they can be bought back with Diamonds ( ) under the decorations section in the Market. In total, it costs 222,800 to remove all obstacles from the island.

Castle[]

Main article: Castle

To be placed on an island, each Monster requires a specific number of beds. For Natural Monsters, this is equal to the number of elements that Monster represents. Ethereal, Supernatural, Legendary, Seasonal, and Mythical Monsters each have varied bed requirements. Upgrade the Castle to unlock more beds.

Sound[]

The Castle also contributes to Plant Island's song. It makes a bass sound.

Seasonal Events[]

Main article: Seasonal Events

During the holiday season of Spooktacle, Plant Island is adorned with Spooktacle decorations. As part of the Spooktacle celebration, all obstacles are changed to Seasonal versions. Limited-time Spooktacle-themed costumes also become available to buy with Diamonds. To see Monster costumes, go here.

Small Spooktacle Tree

Cost: 2 Medium Spooktacle Tree

Cost: 6 Big Spooktacle Tree

Cost: 10 Small Spooktacle Rock

Cost: 4 Medium Spooktacle Rock

Cost: 10 Big Spooktacle Rock

Cost: 20

A special Seasonal Monster, the Punkleton, is available for breeding or purchase in the Market during the Spooktacle season. It was released on October 24th, 2012. Another special Seasonal Monster, the Rare Punkleton, is also available for breeding or purchase in the Market, although only for a limited amount of time during the Spooktacle season. It was released on October 15th, 2016. A special Seasonal Monster, the Epic Punkleton is available for breeding or purchase in the Market, although only for a limited amount of time during the Spooktacle season. It was released on October 16th, 2019.

Notes[]

Version 1.0.4 of My Singing Monsters was released on October 23rd, which included the first celebration of Spooktacle.

Plant Island's full song is 2 minutes and 59 seconds long, which makes it the 2nd longest song in the original My Singing Monsters game, only barely being surpassed by Amber Island, which is 3 minutes long. This also makes Plant Island the 3rd longest song in the franchise after the Continent with a length of 3 minutes and 12 seconds and Amber Island.

Plant Island and Shugabush Island share the same ambience.

Plant Island is the only Natural Island in the game to not have a Monster that plays throughout the entire song.

In fact, the only thing that does play throughout the entire Plant Island song is the Castle bass, possibly to make up for that.

Wubbox is technically the only one to play though the whole song, as it plays a sound in its idle animation.

During the Spooktacle season, there seems to be a strange glow on the island's face. It is unknown what this glow is, or where its coming from.

Initially, before the Werdos came out, Fwog used to transition after Mammott & Toe Jammer finished playing, and Clamble used to play on the part where Oaktopus originally first played.

The Official Soundtrack sounds are different from the in-game sounds.

Drumpler's in-game sound is made out of Drumpler's only drumroll in the Official Soundtrack, which makes it seem "glitchy".

Fwog's in-game sound is slightly different in pitch than its official sound.

Potbelly's front head has a different voice in-game than it is in the official soundtrack.

Maw's second sound for the official soundtrack does not exist in the game.

The Castle is much louder in the Official Soundtrack.

According to Dave Kerr, Plant Island was first composed around December 2011.

In Version 3.8.1, there was a bug with the Colossal where, after going into the Market and then exiting the Market, even if the Colossal was awoken prior to entering the Market, the Colossal's eyes would be closed. This has since been fixed.

As of Version 3.9.2, if you do not have the Werdos or all the Wubboxes, there is a chance of Maw's first verse not playing at all, but Mammott's second verse still playing. When this happens, Clamble's second track plays before Rare Wubbox's verse, but stops its animation (but not its sound) when the verse begins. It does not play at the second time when Rare Wubbox plays its track.

As of Version 3.8.4, because of the reworked Colossal Conundra mechanics, if you completed the Plant Island Conundra before the update, you can have the Plant Island Colossal in a state where it still plays its sound, but the eyes are closed.

As of March 8, 2024, Plant Island's song has received 2 minor revisions since the Colossal, Grennitch, was added.

The first revision was on Version 3.9.2, which extended Fwog's track. Originally, the audio file was ~6.86 seconds long and played 3 times in a row. Since this update, the audio file was made 4 times as long, containing the original audio 3 times in a row, with some extra blank space before and after.

Prior to Version 2.0.4, Fwog's track played 4 times in a row, which was changed when the Werdos were added.

The second revision was on Version 3.9.4, which cleaned up the Dipsters' tracks. Originally, seemingly random notes would be cut off and only last a quarter of the other notes. This was fixed in this update, making it so that nearly all the Dipsters' notes were played for the same length. A few were missed, however.

It is one of the few Islands in the franchise to have at least 1 new Monster be added onto the island per year for more than a decade. (2012-2023).
